              "question": "What is a Fixed Deposit?",
              "answer": "A Fixed Deposit (FD) is a financial instrument provided by banks and NBFCs that offers a higher rate of interest than a regular savings account."
            },
            {
              "glFaqItemId": "general-2",
              "question": "What is the minimum tenure for FD?",
              "answer": "The minimum tenure for FD can be as low as 7 days, depending on the bank."
            }
          ]
        },
